'''Samuel''' "'''Samú'''" '''de Almeida Costa''' (born 27 November 2000) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

==Club career==
===Braga===
Born in [[Aveiro, Portugal|Aveiro]], Costa represented [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]], [[G.D. Gafanha|Gafanha]], Palmeiras FC de Braga and [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] as a youth. He made his [[2019–20 Campeonato de Portugal|Campeonato de Portugal]] debut for the latter's [[S.C. Braga B|B-team]] on 2 November 2019 in a game against [[GD Bragança|Bragança]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/11/02/portugal/ii-divisao/sporting-braga-b/gd-braganca/3106926/ |title=Sporting Braga II vs. Bragança|date=2 November 2019}}</ref>

On 25 July 2020, Costa played his first match for Braga, coming on as a substitute for [[Pedro Amador (footballer)|Pedro Amador]] in the 46th minute in a match against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/07/25/portugal/portuguese-liga-/sporting-braga/futebol-clube-do-porto/3064947/ |title=Sporting Braga vs. Porto|date=25 July 2020}}</ref>

===Almería===
On 10 September 2020, Costa was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[UD Almería]] for the [[2020–21 Segunda División|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticia/samu-costa-un-todo-terreno-para-el-centro-del-campo|title=Samú Costa, un todo terreno para el centro del campo|trans-title=Samú Costa, an all-round for the centre of midfield|publisher=UD Almería|language=es|date=10 September 2020|accessdate=10 September 2020}}</ref> He made his debut abroad seventeen days later, starting in a 2–0 away win over [[CD Lugo]].

Costa scored his first professional goal on 24 January 2021, netting the opener in a 2–2 home draw against [[CE Sabadell FC]]. On 11 June, after being regularly used, he was bought outright and signed a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/almeria/2021/06/11/60c32174268e3e99568b462a.html|title=El Almería hace efectiva la opción de compra por Samú Costa|trans-title=Almería exercise the buyout clause over Samú Costa|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=11 June 2021|accessdate=10 August 2023}}</ref>

Costa helped the [[Andalusia]]ns in their [[2021–22 Segunda División|promotion]] to [[La Liga]] as champions, and made his top-tier debut on 14 August 2022, starting in a 2–1 home loss to [[Real Madrid]]. On 23 September, he further extended his link until 2029.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticias/samu-costa-renueva-hasta-2029|title=Samú Costa renueva hasta 2029|trans-title=Samú Costa renews until 2029|publisher=UD Almería|language=es|date=23 September 2022|accessdate=10 August 2023}}</ref>

===Mallorca===
On 10 August 2023, Costa agreed to a five-year contract with [[RCD Mallorca]] also in the Spanish first division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcdmallorca.es/noticias/samu-costa-se-convierte-en-nuevo-jugador-del-rcd-mallorca|title=Samu Costa se convierte en nuevo jugador del RCD Mallorca|trans-title=Samu Costa becomes the new player of RCD Mallorca|publisher=RCD Mallorca|language=es|date=10 August 2023|accessdate=10 August 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
On 12 October 2024, Costa debuted for [[Portugal national football team]] in a 2–1 victory against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] during a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|UEFA Nations League]] match, coming as a substitute for [[Bernardo Silva]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Cesar|last=Mateu|title=Samú Costa debuta con Portugal y su foco internacional se expande|trans-title=Samú Costa debuts with Portugal and his international focus expands|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/mallorca/2024/10/13/670b908d22601deb528b458c.html|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|publisher=Unidad Editorial|date=13 October 2024|access-date=11 November 2024|language=es}}</ref>

